cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.PF. 

The paper deals with content distribution and caching, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of a Markov model and the analysis of long-term average rate suggest a systems and control perspective (cs.SY). The proposal of an online coded caching scheme and the simulation results indicate a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the comparison with the popular LRU caching algorithm suggests a potential interest in performance evaluation and optimization (cs.PF).
